Kerberos common error

KDC_ERR_S_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN   if SPN is not register
KDC_ERR_c_PRINCIPAL_UNKNOWN ---client issue, need to check the user upn
KRB_AP_ERR_MODIFIED-----this is when the TGS can't be decrypt it, indicate the provided tgs can't be decypt, need to check if the spn is registered
KDC_ERR_ETYPE_NOSUPP----is about encryption type support by client itself. This could ne btw the client and DC
Kdc_ERR_BADOPTION-----error send by kdc the option request by the client or app is not proper, you need to check if the delegation is set correctly
KDC_ERR_policy-----if there is a trust between the forest

